This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with face recognition and image processing. It may also belong to the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR) as it focuses on detecting morphing attacks at automated border control gates. Additionally, the paper uses machine learning techniques, which could place it in the sub-categories of multimedia (cs.MM), machine learning (cs.LG), and information retrieval (cs.IR).
